  "market_context": "Price had formed a bearish structure with multiple breaks of structure, established equal lows (sellside liquidity), then retraced upward to mitigate a large bearish order block but left significant inefficiency. It used the last supply zone as inducement, swept buyside liquidity above an internal high, and tapped into the large unmitigated 4H supply zone before reversing down.",
  "key_observation": "Price reversed sharply downward after tapping into the unmitigated 4H supply zone (1.12400–1.12700) without fully mitigating it, confirming seller control and triggering a short entry after CHoCH on lower timeframe.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a bearish market structure on EURUSD 1H with prior break of structure and formation of equal lows (sellside liquidity) around 1.11200.",
    "Step 2: Noted price reversed upward, mitigated part of a large bearish order block but left significant unmitigated portion (inefficiency/voids) in the 4H supply zone (1.12400–1.12700).",
    "Step 3: Observed price used the last supply zone as inducement, swept buyside liquidity above an internal high, and retested the large 4H supply zone.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed price entered the 4H supply zone, showed rejection (wick or close below zone), and formed a change of character pattern on lower timeframe.",
    "Step 5: Entered a short position at the tap into the unmitigated 4H supply zone, targeting the sellside liquidity at the equal lows (1.11200)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Short position taken at tap into 4H supply zone; price reversed strongly downward toward sellside liquidity (equal lows), achieving favorable risk-to-reward.",
  "lessons": "Unmitigated supply zones on HTF act as high-probability reversal areas when price returns after liquidity sweeps and inducements; CHoCH on LTF confirms entry timing for shorts in bearish structure.",
